In other words, when Monty opens either curtain 2 or 3, revealing small prize behind it, he is giving additional information and changing the odds. Now, the prize is behind the other curtain 66.6 percent of times. In bridge, the same logic is used to explain the restricted choice. Therefore, when missing two touching honors and on the first round one of the defendant plays one honor you should finesse the other for the second honor instead of playing for drop.  |
