a) Play the Ace (or King). If neither the Queen nor Jack drops play the King (or Ace) next and hope for the 2-2 break.

b) If the Queen or Jack appears on the first round, assume the missing honor is in the other hand (the hand which did not drop the honor) and finesse for it. If you do so, the odds of the finesse working are 2 to 1 in your favor.

The reason that play works is as follows. After the first trick (when an honor drops), the only possible distributions of the defenders cards are xx opposite QJ, Jxx opposite Q, or Qxx opposite J. So, in 2 cases out of 3, the finesse works (hence the 2 to 1 odds)."|
